   </font>
   <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
    <br/>
    There is a sign known as "FOR-FOR."
    <br/>
    The sign "FOR-FOR"
    <font face="Arial">
     is the same as "FOR" except that you use a double motion and you include a "wh?" facial expression.
     <br/>
     This sign
    </font>
    is interpreted as "What for?" or
  "Why?"
    <br/>
    <br/>
    FOR-FOR:
    <br/>
    <font face="Arial">
     <img border="0" src="/images/for-for.gif" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto" width="480"/>
    </font>
